<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-12">
    <div id="checker-schema" class="fade modal" tabindex="-1">
      <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="modal-header alert alert-info">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
            <h4 class="modal-title">Checker Grader Schema</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            <ul>
              <li>The Checker grader accepts either individual Java
                files, or archive files (tar, zip, or tar.gz)</li>
              <li>If an archive file, the archive must contain the
                following four directories, which must each be non-empty:
                <ul>
                  <li><code>starter/src</code></li>
                  <li><code>starter/test</code></li>
                  <li><code>testing/src</code></li>
                  <li><code>testing/test</code></li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>The grader will copy the <code>starter</code> files
                into the compilation directory, then the students'
                files, and finally copy the <code>testing</code>
                files.  This ensures that student code cannot
                overwrite instructor tests.</li>
              <li>There must be a Java that contains a package-scoped
              class with the same name as specified in the
                grader.</li>
              <li>You may specify multiple test classes on the
                command-line, to make it easier to organize the test
                cases.  Additionally, you may specify
                <code>weight</code>s to multiply all existing test
                weights within the test classes, to easily manage
                regression testing.  For example:
                <code>ClassA -weight 2 ClassB ClassC -weight 0.5 ClassD</code>
                would give <code>ClassA</code> a
                default weight of 1, classes <code>ClassB</code>
                and <code>ClassC</code> a weight of 2,
                and <code>ClassD</code> a weight of 0.5
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Here is a short example Checker grader test file layout:</p>
            <pre>CheckerGrading.zip
├── starter
│   ├── src
│   │   └── .ignore
│   └── test
│       └── .ignore
└── testing
    ├── src
    │   └── bouncing.jar
    └── test
        └── hw1acc-p5-tests.java</pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
